https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/services-networking/network-policies/

rules should look like this:

# if only except roule 
table inet filter {
	chain forward {
		ct mark 0x1 and 0x1 ip saddr 93.202.132.0/24 drop;
		ct mark 0x1 and 0x1 accept;
	}
}

# if only allow roule 
table inet filter {
	chain forward {
		ct mark 0x1 and 0x1 ip saddr 93.202.132.0/24 accept;
		ct mark 0x1 and 0x1 drop;
	}
}

# if ingress rule exsists but no ip block
table inet filter {
	chain forward {
		ct mark 0x1 and 0x1 drop;
	}
}


is order important?
